Toptal is an exclusive talent network made up of the world’s top 3% of developers, connecting the best and brightest freelancers with top organizations. Unlike a 9-to-5 job, you’ll choose your own schedule and work from anywhere. Jobs come to you, so you won’t bid for projects against other developers in a race to the bottom.   • Full-time availability is a strong advantage


If you’re interested in pursuing an engaging career working on full-time freelance jobs for exclusive clients, take the next step by clicking apply and filling out the short form: https://topt.al/55cX2m

jobs.title: Senior Strategy Analyst
jobs.description:
About Rumin8 Rumin8 is tackling one of the biggest contributors to climate change: methane emissions from livestock. The digestive process of beef and dairy cattle accounts for a full 3.7% of all greenhouse gas emissions, a huge contribution from a single source. With billions of people around the world relying on animal proteins as part of their daily diet, eliminating livestock methane production is a powerful lever in the quest toward a climate-optimal future. Rumin8 has invented a technology that has been shown to reduce the emissions from cattle by up to 95%. Our technology productizes the anti-methane compounds that occur naturally in plants and turns them into dietary supplements for livestock. The results are a reduction in methane emissions by up to 95%, increase in efficiency of the animalâs digestive systems, and more energy for the animal to grow. With recent backing by top climate tech VC investors to commercialize the technology globally, we are on a mission to decarbonize hundreds of millions of cattle around the world so the global food system can take a giant step forward. If you believe - like we do - that solving climate change is the greatest calling of our generation and want to get in on the ground floor with us to tackle it, letâs talk. #LI-Remote About the Role As Rumin8 continues to develop its product offering and prepare for launch, we need to fully understand the global landscape of animal agriculture. As our first Senior Strategy Analyst, youâll be the brain trust for all things pertaining to this industry, conducting deep research on the strategic questions most pressing to us and building out extensive market intelligence to empower the company and inform the executive team. Demonstrating relentless curiosity and resourcefulness, you will build our strategic knowledge base, fulfilling internal requests for information and following your own judgment with self-guided discovery. Your insights will shape our commercialization and market entry strategy, and inform all areas of our company. **Please note: this role is based in the US though the company is currently headquartered in Perth, Australia. You'll be working on a contract basis to begin with as a result. We are beginning to review applications October 5th. At Rumin8, we don't just accept differences, we celebrate them. We know that diverse teams are the strongest teams. We actively strive to eliminate all manners of discrimination and to enable all qualified humans to collaborate on the massive challenges we are undertaking. Addressing climate change is a challenge worthy of our greatest minds, in all varieties. We know that you will make a positive impact with your unique perspectives, background, and experiences. Our team is excited to build something awesome with you, so come as you are.

jobs.title: Risk Associate
jobs.description:
Abra is on a mission to create a simple and honest crypto bank to enable millions of crypto holders to maximize the potential of their crypto assets. We operate an easy to use app allowing users to earn interest, buy, sell, hold, and trade in cryptocurrencies, in one single place. Our vision is an open, global financial system that is easily accessible to everyone by making cryptocurrency investing simple and accessible. Our growing crypto investing and wealth management platform is used by millions of consumers in over 150 countries and growing!

We are growing our team to match our growing user base. This is an opportunity to join a company that is part of the biggest financial revolution in modern history.

Our Risk team is looking for a Risk Associate who will assist the CRO in all aspects of risk management. In this role you will ensure that risks assumed are properly monitored, assessed, reported, and managed in accordance with Abraâs risk policies and risk appetite.

What Youâll Do:

  • Monitor, identify, and escalate risk issues for the trading and lending books (to cover non-US hours)
  • Enhance intraday risk monitoring and management capabilities
  • Define and implement risk metrics risk measurement and reporting
  • Monitor and measure the effectiveness of the risk framework; recommend changes as required
  • Monitor the market environment and risk model performance
  • Collaborate with other teams (Credit, Trading, Operations, Analytics, Sales, etc.) in developing new and improving existing analytics and quantitative models for measuring risk
  • Stay abreast of regional changes to rules/regulations
  • Support ad-hoc risk analysis and initiatives

About You:

  • A motivated self-starter with strong organization skills and experience setting priorities, problem-solving, and multi-tasking
  • Strong intellect, a broad perspective, an ability to think strategically, and the confidence to interact with a wide-range of personnel
  • Excellent written and spoken communicator with ability to translate complex risk topics into actionable tasks

What Youâll Need:

  • Over 5 years of demonstrated experience in risk management/trading/ops in financial services, previous experience in crypto preferred
  • Solid understanding of derivatives and options
  • Experience in developing and managing quantitative risk measurement models, designing and interpreting stress testing analyses

Full-Time Employee Benefits:

  • Globally distributed team (everyone is remote!)
  • Unlimited PTO
  • Medical
  • Dental
  • Vision
  • Basic and supplemental life insurance
  • Short-term and long-term disability
  • 401(k)

At Abra, we are an equal opportunity employer committed to a diverse, inclusive, and equitable workplace and candidate experience. We strive to create an environment where everyone has a sense of belonging and purpose, and where we learn from the unique experiences of those around us.

We encourage all qualified candidates to apply regardless of race, color, ancestry, religion, national origin, sexual orientation, age, citizenship, marital or family status, disability, gender, gender identity or expression, pregnancy or caregiver status, veteran status, or any other legally protected status.

jobs.title: Data Scientist
jobs.description:
Who are we?

PredictHQ is the leading source of demand intelligence, enabling global companies to accurately predict and prepare for demand anomalies. Our vision is to predict the catalyst behind any form of demand.

We cover every major category from conferences and concerts to live, unscheduled events such as extreme weather or airport delays. Our expertise is in verifying, enriching, and adding intelligence to the millions of significant events that impact demand, so companies can act before it's too late.

Our teams are creating advanced machine learning algorithms, using data from thousands of sources around the world, processing it through our modern, microservices based pipeline - and exposing it to customers via a powerful API. Some of the world’s most exciting companies such as Uber, Amazon Alexa, Accor Hotels, and Domino’s Pizza rely on us to learn from the past and predict their future.

Launched in 2016, PredictHQ is growing rapidly and backed by Lightspeed Venture Partners, Sutter Hill Ventures, and Aspect Ventures. PredictHQ has offices in Auckland, New Zealand, San Francisco, US, and London, UK.

Our team combines the best of the American ambition and drive with New Zealand’s empathy and community spirit. We have high standards and huge plans.

Requirements

We are on the hunt for an NLP data scientist with experience in advanced text analytics to help us enhance and enrich our demand intelligence platform. This can be a Remote Opportunity in New Zealand or work from our office in Auckland - you can live anywhere in New Zealand with access to solid WIFI, and work remotely from the comfort of your home office. Candidates will need to reside in New Zealand with full-working rights.

You will be using the latest techniques such as modern NLP algorithms, machine learning modelling and advanced statistical modelling to solve complex problems within a cutting-edge development environment. Working closely with our data scientists and data analysts, and within a cross-functional team to solve complex problems using both data science and intelligent analytical solutions. This exciting opportunity will see the solutions you help create being integrated directly into our product and being used by many of the world’s most recognisable companies.

You will be working within a business that is focused on a shared vision of growing globally and continuing to deliver a unique platform across a diversified set of customers. This role will be immensely rewarding and you will be working alongside an experienced and passionate team who have been involved in starting up businesses that now employ hundreds of staff across the world.

A Data Scientist at PredictHQ will:

  • R&D advanced machine learning algorithms, advanced analytical modelling, and NLP models to deliver, enhance and enrich our demand intelligence features and products
  • Build large-scale NLP solutions from researching a prototype to production
  • Proactively enhance and improve current intelligence features and models
  • Work with data and dev teams to deliver data intelligence

Skills, Knowledge and Competencies:

  • 2 years in a data scientist role with Statistics/Mathematics/Computer Science background
  • Experience in building large-scale NLP solutions from researching a prototype to production
  • Essential skills include critical thinking, NLP techniques, machine learning algorithms, and analytical programming
  • Essential technical skills in SQL and Python
  • Must have experience of R&D in data science

You may not have experience with all of the technologies mentioned above, but as long as you have a passion for learning, then our team will help and support you. Data and data quality is of the utmost importance to us, and your work should reflect this, so you should have excellent attention to detail.

Our people come first

Enabling and supporting them to do their best work is a company priority. Regardless of age, education, ethnicity, gender, sexual orientation or any personal characteristics, we want everyone to feel welcome. Our PredictHQ values are at the heart of our business and mean we are not only creating a word-first product but also a culture that is inclusive and unique.

General

  • Applicants for this position must have New Zealand residency or a valid New Zealand work visa
  • Ensure that all activities are conducted in accordance with internal policies and procedures, applicable legislation, rules and standards, including relevant Acts, Advertising Standards Authority rules and regulations, and industry body requirements

Benefits

  • Hybrid work environment centred on collaboration, flexibility, agility, and fun
  • Health Insurance
  • Paid Birthday Leave & Paid Family and Friends Day Leave
  • 10 weeks fully paid Parental Leave
  • Stock options in a fast-growing company in its early stages
  • Strong focus on your training and development
  • Regular social events (we can't be the event experts if we don't have a few of our own!)
